        <div class="body">
            <p>No, this is not a problem...
You said that you want to have the ISO Year instead of the real year.</p>

<p>This is normally used when you want to calculate calendars.
Week 1 of the Calendarsheet 2008 begins with 31.December.</p>

<p>If you need to have the real year, you should define it within your userformat.</p>

<p>"Y" = ISO-Year
"y" = Real-Year</p>

